WRITING.TITLE: Any electricians here? Need help with wire sizes for Induction hob
WRITING.TEXT: Good day guys, I would like to install an induction hob in my kitchen. However as I live in UAE they mainly use gas here which I hate. My house currently has a 4mm wire and 20A breaker. Induction hob is rated at 7.4kW. I wanna change the wiring but since my conduit is only 25mm I am kinda limited. Electrician said he will pull 2x 10mm wires and 1x4mm wire for grounding and 40A circuit breaker. Is this safe? Can I install 3x 6mm wires and like 32A CB and be safe. Main concern is fire hazard? Thanks

I was talking to some electricians and they say since I wont use all 4 at the same time when starting the hob even 4mm and like 25A would be fine. Some other electricians say 6mm and 32A is fine. Am a bit confused who to believe because if something goes wrong I will have to pay for it. Maybe I am just paranoid for no reason.
